Trimming:

Trimming involves removing outliers from the dataset entirely. You can choose to remove a
fixed percentage of the extreme values from both ends of the distribution.

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

# Create a sample dataframe with outliers
data = {
    'X': [1, 2, 3, 4, 10, 20, 30, 40, 100]
}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Trim the top and bottom 10% of values
lower_percentile = df['X'].quantile(0.1)
upper_percentile = df['X'].quantile(0.9)
df_trimmed = df[(df['X'] >= lower_percentile) & (df['X'] <= upper_percentile)]

print(df_trimmed)
